      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Intriguing race with lots of talent engaged. TAROONA (4) is the in-form galloper and looks hard to beat again. Has won his last two on the Devonport Synthetic and will take catching again. THE REAL MAN (5) is in similar form, just missing off a wide gate two back then scoring latest. Draws well and another big run is in store. Hard to line up TEMPT THE GODS (1). Victorian who a few runs ago was Stakes placed while travelling here last summer. Fitter for two runs back and returns to Tassie but coming off a terrible run last time in heavy ground at Ballarat when on pace but dropping right out. Best form stacks up, and given he's still come over may well be worth another chance. ZAMBEZI BLONDE (3) is a promising type resuming and is building a strong record. Has good upside and is capable of a bold return. DAYTONA DIVA (2) may find this a bit sharp and is a stakes winner here of the Strutt Stakes just two back. Does go well fresh though and will be winding up late.",
